Uses of Package
de.mslab.ciphers

  • Packages that use de.mslab.ciphers 
    Package Description
    de.mslab.applications
    Provides application classes for biclique search, matching, and rendering.
    de.mslab.bicliquesearch
    Provides classes which implement the biclique finding process.
    de.mslab.ciphers
    Provides classes which represent implementations of popular block ciphers.
    de.mslab.ciphers.helpers
    Provides helper classes which count the number of active bits or bytes in non-linear operations in the matching phase for the individual block ciphers.
    de.mslab.diffbuilder
    Provides helper classes which are required for biclique creation, such as to construct differences for bit-wise or byte-wise operating ciphers, or to compare differentials for their independency.
    de.mslab.matching
    Provides classes which are required to compute the matching part of biclique attacks, and to compute the complexity of biclique attacks.
    de.mslab.rendering
    Provides classes which are responsible to render bicliques, matching phases, and the contained differentials, with state and key differences at their rounds.
  • Classes in de.mslab.ciphers used by de.mslab.applications 
    Class and Description
    CipherFactory.CipherName
    List of ciphers which can be specified by the user calling the resulting jar of the BicliqueFinderApplication with the console.
  • Classes in de.mslab.ciphers used by de.mslab.bicliquesearch 
    Class and Description
    RoundBasedBlockCipher
    Interface for all symmetric ciphers which employ a round-based encryption or decryption.
  • Classes in de.mslab.ciphers used by de.mslab.ciphers 
    Class and Description
    AES
    Abstract base class for the AES, as designed 1998 as Rijndael by Daemen and Rijmen.
    ARIA
    Abstract base class for the ARIA block cipher, the South-Korean equivalent to the AES standardized 2003/2004.
    BlockCipher
    Interface for all symmetric ciphers.
    CipherFactory.CipherName
    List of ciphers which can be specified by the user calling the resulting jar of the BicliqueFinderApplication with the console.
    LED
    Implements the LED block cipher, designed 2011 by Guo, Peyrin and al.
    PRESENT
    Implements the PRESENT ultra-lightweight block cipher, designed 2007 by Bogdanov, Knudsen et al.
    RoundBasedBlockCipher
    Interface for all symmetric ciphers which employ a round-based encryption or decryption.
    ThreeFish
    Implements the ThreeFish block cipher, which serves as the block cipher used in Skein, and was designed 2009 by Ferguson, Lucks, Schneier et al.
    TweakableCipher
    Interface for round-based symmetric ciphers which employ a tweak as an additional parameter for encryption or decryption, such as ThreeFish.
